---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

const baseUrl = import.meta.env.BASE_URL;
const basePath = baseUrl.endsWith('/') ? baseUrl : `${baseUrl}/`;
---

<BaseLayout title="Projects | Robert Otieno" description="Selected architecture and IAM projects by Robert Otieno.">
	<section class="hero" style="margin-top: 0;">
		<div>
		<p class="eyebrow">Selected Work</p>
		<h1>Enterprise Security and Identity Systems</h1>
		<p class="lead">A focused set of projects demonstrating architecture depth, governance rigor, and operational scalability.</p>
		<div class="cta-row">
			<a class="cta" href={`${basePath}portfolio/`}>Open Full Portfolio</a>
			<a class="cta" href={`${basePath}about/`}>About Approach</a>
		</div>
		</div>
		<div class="hero-art" aria-hidden="true">
			<svg viewBox="0 0 420 280" width="100%">
				<rect x="40" y="36" width="340" height="54" rx="8" fill="#ffffff" stroke="#cbd5e1" />
				<rect x="40" y="110" width="160" height="120" rx="8" fill="#ffffff" stroke="#cbd5e1" />
				<rect x="220" y="110" width="160" height="120" rx="8" fill="#f8faff" stroke="#1e3a8a" />
				<text x="58" y="68" fill="#1f2937" font-size="13">Case Studies · Decisions · Trade-offs · Outcomes</text>
				<text x="58" y="145" fill="#1f2937" font-size="12">Problem</text>
				<text x="58" y="170" fill="#1f2937" font-size="12">Architecture</text>
				<text x="58" y="195" fill="#1f2937" font-size="12">Security</text>
				<text x="238" y="145" fill="#1e3a8a" font-size="12">Governance</text>
				<text x="238" y="170" fill="#1e3a8a" font-size="12">Automation</text>
				<text x="238" y="195" fill="#1e3a8a" font-size="12">Impact</text>
			</svg>
		</div>
	</section>

	<section>
		<article class="card">
			<h2>Decentralized Employment Verification System</h2>
			<p>Architected a trust-based employment verification system using Verifiable Credentials and decentralized identity infrastructure.</p>
			<h3>Problem</h3>
			<p>Traditional verification workflows were slow, high-friction, and difficult to audit across organizational boundaries.</p>
			<h3>Architectural Decisions</h3>
			<ul>
				<li>Verifiable credential lifecycle model for issuance and revocation</li>
				<li>Selective disclosure patterns for data minimization</li>
				<li>Modular service boundaries for policy and trust control</li>
			</ul>
			<h3>Security Considerations and Trade-offs</h3>
			<ul>
				<li>Balanced decentralization benefits with governance requirements</li>
				<li>Designed for auditability without overexposure of identity data</li>
				<li>Prioritized integration pathways for enterprise environments</li>
			</ul>
			<p><strong>Outcome:</strong> A privacy-centric verification model that supports enterprise integration without sacrificing trust controls.</p>
		</article>
	</section>

	<section>
		<article class="card">
			<h2>Enterprise IAM & Access Governance Optimization</h2>
			<p>Improved identity lifecycle governance and operational access controls in enterprise IT environments.</p>
			<h3>Problem</h3>
			<p>Manual provisioning and inconsistent review cycles introduced risk and operational delay.</p>
			<h3>Architectural Decisions</h3>
			<ul>
				<li>Role and access lifecycle standardization</li>
				<li>Operational integration between IAM and IT service controls</li>
				<li>Automation-first approach for recurring governance workflows</li>
			</ul>
			<h3>Impact Areas</h3>
			<ul>
				<li>Reduced manual access provisioning effort</li>
				<li>Strengthened access review reliability</li>
				<li>Improved audit readiness and governance consistency</li>
			</ul>
			<p><strong>Outcome:</strong> A more resilient and operationally sustainable IAM governance model.</p>
		</article>
	</section>
</BaseLayout>